body:
Sorry I should have specified. I would like to use the C# binding and the `Microsoft.ML.Onnxruntime.Gpu` nuget package to detect objects using ONNX in ML.Net. In my project, I have a Yolo Darknet model I've trained from an image set using the following python script: https://gist.github.com/celowsky/a708870e2b316b592dc3c48ad2a3e16b.

I called the script like this: `python --img 416 --batch 16 --epochs 5 --data data\data.yaml --cfg models\yolov5x.yaml --weights weights\yolov5x.pt`

In my WinForms application, I click a button on my form to trigger the following function:
```c#
        private void OnLoadTrainingClick(object sender, EventArgs e)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Detect image path is " + _detectImagesPath);
            this.mlContext = new MLContext();
            var capturer = new ScreenCapture();
            Bitmap windowImage = GetWindowBitmap();
            this.myBitmap = windowImage;
            this.myImage = new ImageNetData { Image = windowImage };
            this.images = new List<ImageNetData>();
            this.dataView = mlContext.Data.LoadFromEnumerable<ImageNetData>(this.images);
            var scorer = new OnnxModelScorer(_modelPath, this.mlContext, this.images);
            IEnumerable<float[]> probabilities = scorer.Score(this.dataView);
            YoloOutputParser parser = new YoloOutputParser();
            IEnumerable<IList<YoloBoundingBox>> boundingBoxes = probabilities
                .Select(probability => parser.ParseOutputs(probability))
                .Select(boxes => parser.FilterBoundingBoxes(boxes, 5, .5F));
            var imageName = Guid.NewGuid() + ".bmp";
            var image = DrawBoundingBox(imageName, windowImage);

            image.Save(Path.Combine(_detectImagesPath, imageName));
        }
```

The following line from the above snippet fails: `IEnumerable<float[]> probabilities = scorer.Score(this.dataView);`. 
Following the call stack leads me to the same error as the author of this issue: 
```
System.TypeInitializationException: 'The type initializer for 'Microsoft.ML.OnnxRuntime.NativeMethods' threw an exception.'
DllNotFoundException: Unable to load DLL 'onnxruntime': The specified module could not be found. (Exception from HRESULT: 0x8007007E)
```
Most of the classes here are either identical or lightly adapted from this Microsoft tutorial: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/machine-learning/tutorials/object-detection-onnx

Here are the exact classes I'm using:
OnnxModelScorer.cs: https://gist.github.com/celowsky/8c9c2435d547ec4d26f06af69b5a18ec
YoloOutputParser.cs: https://gist.github.com/celowsky/c88152146107a26e602cf717fd092e44
YoloBoundingBox.cs: https://gist.github.com/celowsky/f8a2618c89ab38cb2ef356e977cbc4a2
